{"lemma":"مُخٌّ","slug":"مُخٌّ","root":"م.خ.خ","root_slug":"م-خ-خ","root_link":"/words/roots/م-خ-خ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38268"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AE%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cerebrum"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *muḫḫ- (“head; brain; marrow”)."},"ipa":["/muxx/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38268","headword_ar":"مُخٌّ","root":"mx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"marrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqoY","text_ar":"نِقْى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naqiY~","text_ar":"نَقِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a bone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which is in a bone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substance which is extracted from a bone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"greasy"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"oily substance which is in a bone:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mixaxapN","text_ar":"مِخَخَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mixaAxN","text_ar":"مِخَاخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any kind of pulp."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mux~apN","text_ar":"مُخَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a more special term than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mux~N","text_ar":"مُخٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece, of marrow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N m~aA yujiyuw^ka A_ilaY mux~api EuroquwbK","text_ar":"شَرٌّ مَّا يُجِيُوكَ اـِلَى مُخَّةِ عُرْقُوبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is an evil thing that compelleth thee to have recourse to the marrow of a hock"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. A proverb. (S.) [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Erqb","text_ar":"عرقب"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mux~N","text_ar":"مُخٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (sometimes, S,) (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b6-  Also, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulb"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit. fat,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aHomap","text_ar":"شَحْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of the eye. (A, K.) Mostly used in this sense in poetry. (TA.) ―         -b7-  Also, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Good, profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advantage."},{"kind":"text","text":"Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^araY","text_ar":"لَا اَرَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^amorika mux~FA","text_ar":"لِاَمْرِكَ مُخًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I see no good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"advantage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pertaining"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to thy affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2693},{"kind":"text","text":"Also, (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purest, choicest, best,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most excellent, part of anything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mux~apN","text_ar":"مُخَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxaAxapN","text_ar":"مُخَاخَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='u","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mux~u Alqawomi","text_ar":"مُخُّ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mux~atuhumo","text_ar":"مُخَّتُهُمْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are the best of the people."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~uEaA='u mux~u AlEibaAdapi","text_ar":"الدُّعَا=ءُ مُخُّ العِبَادَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Supplication is the purest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best, part of religious worship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devotion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, from a trad.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA mino mux~i qalobiY","text_ar":"هٰذَا مِنْ مُخِّ قَلْبِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mux~atihi","text_ar":"مُخَّتِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proceeds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the purest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"best,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affections"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of my heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","A","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D8%AE/","headword_ar":"مخ","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53710#6decff","body_html":"مخ المخ نقي العظم، والجميع المخخة. وتمخخت العظم. والمخة ما يتخير. ومخ العين شحمها. وأمخ العظم صار ذا مخ. وأمخت الشاة اكتنزت سمناً. وأمخ الرجل مثله. ولسان ممخ ذلق. وفي المثل \" أهون مرزئة لسان ممخ \". ويقولون \" أسمح من مخة الري \"."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_32","lexicon_en":"Supplément aux dictionnaires arabes by Reinhart Dozy (d. 1883 CE)","lexicon_ar":"تكملة المعاجم العربية لرينهارت دوزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53710#29fc93","body_html":"مخ: مخ وجمعها أمخاخ: (فوك، بوشر) مخ الذر= شيء لا وجود له (الثعالبي لطائف 6: 26).<br>مخ السمك: غدة التذكير، غدة في السمكة تحتوي على الرول أو المادة الملقحة) رول، خصى السمك، بيوض، جزء من أحشاء السمكة الذكر مكون من مادة بيضاء ذات رخاوة (بوشر).<br>مخي: نخاعي (بوشر).<br>مخى: دماغي (بوشر)."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=53710#f0d2ac","body_html":"<div>مخ</div><div><br></div><div>مخّخ العَظْمَ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and ↓ تمخّخهُ and ↓ امتخّهُ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and ↓ مَخْمَخَهُ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) He extracted the marrow from the bone. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.)</div><div><br></div><div>4 امخّ It (a bone) was, or became, marrowy; had, or contained, marrow in it. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> It (a camel, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, and a sheep or goat, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>)</div><div><br></div><div>became fat: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) or became in the first stage of fatness; or in the last stage when becoming lean. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> امخّ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) It (a branch, or twig,) became sappy, and succulent. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) It (standing corn, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, or its grain, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>)</div><div><br></div><div>became supplied with the farinaceous substance. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.)</div><div><br></div><div>5 تَمَخَّّ see 1.</div><div><br></div><div>8 إِمْتَخَ3َ see 1.</div><div><br></div><div>R. <abbr title=\"quadriliteral-radical verb, فِعْلٌ رُبَاعِيٌّ\">Q.</abbr> 1 see 1.</div><div><br></div><div>مَخٌّ <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> لِينٌ Softness, &amp;c.: or لَيْنٌ soft, &amp;c. (So in different copies of the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.)</div><div><br></div><div>مُخٌّ The marrow (نِقْى, in the <abbr title=\"The Calcutta edition of the Qāmūs of Firuzabadi\">CK</abbr> نَقِىّ,) of a bone; (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) that which is in a bone; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>;) the substance which is extracted from a bone; (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>;) the greasy or oily substance which is in a bone: (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> مِخَخَةٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and مِخَاخٌ. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> [Any kind of pulp.] </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> ↓ مُخَّةٌ is a more special term than مُخٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) signifying </div><div><br></div><div>A portion, or piece, of marrow. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b4:</span> شَرٌّ مَّا يُجِيُؤكَ إِلَى مُخَّةِ عُرْقُوبٍ [It is an evil thing that compelleth thee to have recourse to the marrow of a hock]. A proverb. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>.) [See art. عرقب.] </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b5:</span> مُخٌّ also signifies (sometimes, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>,) (assumed <abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) The brain. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b6:</span> Also, The bulb (<abbr title=\"literally\">lit.</abbr> fat, شَحْمَة,) of the eye. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) Mostly </div><div><br></div><div>used in this sense in poetry. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b7:</span> Also, (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) Good, profit, or advantage. <abbr title=\"example\">Ex.</abbr> لَا أَرَى</div><div><br></div><div>لِأَمْرِكَ مُخًّا I see no good, or profit, or advantage, [pertaining] to thy affair. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b8:</span> Also, (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) The purest, choicest, best, or most excellent, part of anything: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) and ↓ مُخَّةٌ (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>) and ↓ مُخَاخَةٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <abbr title=\"example\">Ex.</abbr> هٰؤُلَآءُ</div><div><br></div><div>مُخُّ القَوْمِ, and ↓ مُخَّتُهُمْ, (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) These are the best of the people. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) And الدُّعَآءُ مُخُّ العِبَادَةِ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) Supplication is the purest, or best, part of religious worship, or devotion. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, from a <abbr title=\"tradition (hadith), حَدِيْثٌ\">trad.</abbr>) and هٰذَا مِنْ مُخِّ قَلْبِى, and ↓ مُخَّتِهِ, (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) This [proceeds]</div><div><br></div><div>from the purest, or best, [affections] of my heart. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.)</div><div><br></div><div>مُخَّةٌ: see مُخٌّ.</div><div><br></div><div>مَخِيخٌ A bone containing marrow. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> مَخِيخَةٌ A ewe, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and a she-camel, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) having marrow in her bones. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> Also, the latter, (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) An excellent she-camel: (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>:) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> مَخَائِخُ. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.)</div><div><br></div><div>مُخَاخَةٌ What one sucks from a bone; (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>;)</div><div><br></div><div>what comes forth from a bone into the mouth of him who sucks it. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> See مُخٌّ.</div><div><br></div><div>مُمِخٌّ <abbr title=\"active participial noun, اِسْمُ فَاعِلٍ\">act. part. n.</abbr> of أَمَخَّ. </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> بَيْنَ المُمِخَّةِ</div><div><br></div><div>والعَجْفَآءِ [Between the fat she-camel or ewe, and the lean]. A proverb. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) Said of a thing which is of a middling sort. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) </div><div><br></div><div><span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> لِسَانٌ مُمِخٌّ A sharp, or ready, tongue, powerful to speak: and a tongue that intercedes well. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.)</div><div><br></div><div>أَمْرٌ مُمِخٌّ (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and ↓ مُمَخِّخٌ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>,) A thing, or an affair, in which is excellence, and good: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>:) or, that benefits; <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> طَائِلٌ: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) but <abbr title=\"according\">accord.</abbr> to the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, long; <abbr title=\"synonym and synonymous, مَرَادفٌ and مَتَرَادِفٌ\">syn.</abbr> طَوِيلٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.)</div><div><br></div><div>مُمَخِّخٌ: see مُمِخٌّ.</div>"}]}}